	     Harare - Zimbabwe's President Robert Mugabe has fired his deputy Emmerson Mnangagwa, accusing him of being disloyal. The decision removes one of the leading contenders to become Mugabe's successor, amid speculation the president is preparing his wife to take over instead. Many are now questioning how the firing of Mnangagwa, who is still an influential figure, will affect the country. Al Jazeera's Haru Mutasa reports from Harare. Click here to watch the report. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  